references.paper_title: High-resolution image synthesis with latent diffusion models
references.reason: This paper is foundational for understanding the advancements in latent diffusion models which are critical to the generation of high-resolution images and therefore is essential to the paper’s AGID benchmark.

references.paper_title: SDXL: Improving latent diffusion models for high-resolution image synthesis
references.reason: This paper introduces improvements to latent diffusion models, a key component of the paper’s research on AI-generated image detection.

references.paper_title: Scaling rectified flow transformers for high-resolution image synthesis
references.reason: This paper presents further scaling of latent diffusion models, providing a state-of-the-art method for image synthesis relevant to the paper’s AGID analysis.
This paper is a seminal work on zero-shot text-to-image generation, which is directly relevant to the generation methods used in the paper's VCT² benchmark.

references.paper_title: Improving image generation with better captions
references.reason: This paper details improvements in image generation, directly impacting the quality and characteristics of AI-generated images, thus relevant to AGID.
